      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Besides the flickering lights and hard starts, you should also watch for a dimming dashboard, a faint whining sound from the alternator, or a sweet smell of burnt electronics. If you notice any of these, it is a good sign that the alternator is still working but is about to give up. You can also check the battery terminal connections for looseness, as a loose connection can mimic a failing alternator. To avoid being stranded, consider having the alternator tested by a professional using a load test before it completely stops.",
